# Testing Infrastructure
#
# Unified testing tools for Simple programs.
#
# Public API:
#   use std.testing.{assert_eq, assert_true, measure_time, ...}
#   use std.testing.attributes.{timeout, retry, tag, skip_test}
#   use std.testing.{MockFunction, create_mock, verify_called, ...}
#
# Submodules:
#   - helpers: Assertion utilities, timing, collection checks, fixtures
#   - benchmark: Statistical benchmarking with warmup and comparison
#   - deployment: Smoke testing with retry logic and reporting
#   - gpu_helpers: GPU test skipping, fixtures, assertion helpers
#   - attributes: Attribute-based test configuration (timeout, retry, tag)
#   - mocking: Mock re-export module (re-exports core, async, advanced)
#   - mocking_core: Core mocking (call tracking, verification, matchers)
#   - mocking_async: Async/await mocking (promises, timing)
#   - mocking_advanced: Advanced features (scheduling, retry, rate limiting)
#   - mock/: Submodule with builder, verification, spy implementations

# Test helpers and utilities (assertions)
